4.38 .438(Non-Template Classes)J
23 92 :M
f0_12 sf
-.143(Template and non-template classes currently both  inject friend declarations; for template classes it is)A
23 104 :M
-.092(done at instantiation, and for non-template classes it is done at class declaration.  If the proposed)A
23 116 :M
-.123(lookup rule applies only to template classes, there would still be a difference between template and)A
23 128 :M
-.084(non-template classes.  This is neither an advantage nor a disadvantage of the proposed change.)A
23 152 :M
-.061(However, it would be possible to apply the proposed rule to non-template classes too.  That would)A
23 164 :M
-.099(make template and non-template classes very consistent with respect to friend lookup.  This would be)A
23 176 :M
-.103(a significant advantage, although it has the potential for breaking some existing code.)A
23 200 :M
